Ma gave a warm opening speech to all representatives who hailed
from major cities in Asia, including Bangkok, New Delhi, Tokyo,
Singapore, Seoul, Kuala Lumpur, Jakarta, Hanoi, Manila, and Yangon.

Lai proposed a petition to the High Administrative Court March 14
for a ban on U.S. beef imports, but it was later dismissed. However,
the lawmaker has appealed to the Taipei Supreme Administrative Court.

The two-day activity was jointly organized by the TNPA and two
private mountain-climbing clubs, with around 140 people taking part,
TNPA officials said.
